Package: lidR
Type: Package
Title: Airborne LiDAR data manipulation and visualisation for forestry applications
Version: 0.5.0
Date: 2016-03-16
Author: Jean-Romain Roussel
Maintainer: Jean-Romain Roussel <jean-romain.roussel.1@ulaval.ca>
Description: This package provide airborne LiDAR interface for data visualisation and manipulation. It has been designed mainly for forestry application. lidR package allows computation of digital elevation model of canopy, point classification based on geographic shapefiles, space rasterization, computation of derived metric, point filtering, artificial point reduction and others manipulations.
License: GPL-2
Depends: R (>= 3.1.2),methods,dplyr,data.table,magrittr
Imports: rgl,grDevices,reshape2,geometry,tools,parallel,RcppArmadillo,rgeos,fields,bitops,raster,sp,rgdal,plyr
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
